				<div class="p-6">
					<h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3">The Basotho Blanket</h3>
					<p class="text-sm text-emerald-200 leading-relaxed">The national dress revolves around the Basotho blanket, a thick, richly patterned covering originally made of wool, now often acrylic. It is worn as a cloak by men and women in daily life and during ceremonies, and has become an internationally recognized symbol of Basotho identity.</p>
				</div>
